===Transition probability===

To calculate the lifetime of a neutron in a state formula_29 according to the usual quantum perturbation theory, the above matrix elements must be summed over all unoccupied electron and neutrino states. This is simplified by assuming that the electron and neutrino eigenfunctions formula_5 and formula_14 are constant within the nucleus (i.e., their Compton wavelength is much larger than the size of the nucleus). This leads to

:formula_78

where formula_5 and formula_14 are now evaluated at the position of the nucleus.

According to Fermi&#x27;s golden rule, the probability of this transition is

